5: Uhhh... Guess we just wait here then?
8:
This job's from those pirates, right?
Bet you this is gonna be a royal pain
in the fur.
11:
Well, we already accepted, so we're
stuck with it now.
24:
Oh! Are you the ones who're gonna
help with the investigation?
28:
Yeah. I take it you're Floretta. The
other pirates aren't with you?
32:
Nope, they pulled rank and pushed
everything onto me.
34:
Not that I'm a part of their crew
anymore.
38:
...You aren't a member of the
Crimson Blades?
41:
No, I'm a mercenary working for the
Gaean Navy. But a long time ago, I
served a short stint under Captain
Marina.
43: I haven't seen her since, though...
45:
But, you know her. Ahaha, I bet she's
doing just fine, wherever she is...
49:
In any case, what exactly will we be
doing? We only heard that we're
assisting an investigation on
Oceanus.
52: Right, sorry! Please wait a moment.
55:
We're to investigate... glowing
bubbles... off the coast of the Floats?
59:
Why did I just hear a question mark?
Gimme that.
64:
It says here that these mysterious
bubbles appear out of nowhere and
explode to cause serious damage.
67:
The heck? You've gotta be kidding
me.
73:
We should be fine! It's only been
happening in coastal waters and
hasn't sunk any ships... yet!
75:
A-and they only go after pirate
vessels! You know, the kind that
really LOOK like they're out to rob
someone.
80: And... how do you know this?
84:
Oh, just a hunch, ahaha! I
connected some dots, that's all!
88:
Look, we've arrived at the scene of
the crime!
92:
Everything seems normal at first
glance. Is there anything specific we
should be looking for?
96:
Nope, everything looks normal to
me too. Maybe we should call it
quits!
105:
G-get back, everyone! Leave this to
me!
111:
Thanks, but... Nice, uh, exploding
bubbles you got there.
116:
Right? I know I don't look it, but I AM
a mercenary. I've got a trick or two!
120:
What an interesting weapon. A
blade that makes giant, glowing
bubbles. Impressive.
125:
Good eye! It's a one-of-a-kind,
custom-made by a famous
alchemist!
130:
Wow, Floretta. I'm glad we've got an
expert like you to help us investigate
the bubbles blowing up pirate ships.
137:
Thanks for all your help with the
investigation today!
141:
Er... Hmm... Light, what do we do
about this?
145:
Heya, thanks for the help. Sorry we
couldn't pitch in.
150: Oh, hello! It's been a while, hasn't it?
163:
Guess you noticed too, huh? It's
obvious that she's the culprit.
169:
H-how did you—uhhh, I'm afraid I
don't know what you're talking
about!
172:
Sorry, kid, but do you mind taking
care of her? You can tell she ain't a
bad one.
177:
The military's making its move, but
she'll be safe with you.
181: Why did you attack those ships?
186:
I wanted to protect the merchants
from pirates...
187: It wasn't an order from the navy.
192:
Man, if you coulda taken on all those
ships by yourself, you shoulda just
stayed on with the Crimson Blades.
196:
Uhh, 'member all the stuff she
messed up? She's dumber than ME.
201:
I understand the situation now.
Floretta, we will watch over you.
206:
You always pick up strays without
thinking it through... Not that I've got
a right to complain about it.
208: Welcome to the family, Explodey Girl.
213:
S-sorry to be a bother, but I
appreciate it...
217:
A-are we in another world?!
Somebody pinch me...
220:
Is it really okay for me to be here?
I've caused you so much trouble
already.
224:
This isn't our first pirate rodeo.
Besides, we've got plenty of
troublemakers with us already.
What's one more?
229:
Ack... Sorry, guys, I'll do my best not
to mess anything up.
